Another bit of trivia: The Dutch anthem (Het Wilhelmus) is generally considered the first national anthem, with its use, pretty much in the modern form, starting (at least) in 1572. While other anthems use much older pre-existing melodies or lyrics, these only were combined and used as anthems much later.
